(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B7A4C62FFFE6DC7FE80FD33C2A7" author="Warncke" box="[481,663,364,390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="7" refString="Warnicke, K. (1985) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna des Iran 19. - 20. Die gattungen Panurgus Pz. und Meliturgula Fr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Ven ezia, 34, 221 - 235." type="journal article" year="1985">
Warncke, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE6E7DFE80FD33C2A7" box="[603,663,364,390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6EFAFE80FBB8C2A7" authority="Popov, 1967" authorityName="Popov" authorityYear="1967" box="[732,1052,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6EFAFE80FCC8C2A4" box="[732,876,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F.lacrymosa</emphasis>
(Popov, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE6FFEFE80FBB0C2A7" box="[984,1044,364,390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
are well characterized by a yellow and black (wasp­like) coloration, close to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6FF6FE78FA83C28F" authority="Spinola, 1843" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1843" box="[976,1319,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Camptopoeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6FF6FE78FBDFC28C" box="[976,1147,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Camptopoeum</emphasis>
Spinola, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE68CFFE78FA83C28F" box="[1257,1319,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1843.0">1843</number>
</taxonomicName>
. The larger species 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6DD4FE50FC9AC2F7" authority="Warncke, 1985" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1985" box="[498,830,444,470]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserta">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6DD4FE50FDCEC2F4" box="[498,618,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. deserta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B7A4C62FFFE6E5BFE50FC92C2F7" author="Warncke" box="[637,822,444,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="7" refString="Warnicke, K. (1985) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna des Iran 19. - 20. Die gattungen Panurgus Pz. und Meliturgula Fr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Ven ezia, 34, 221 - 235." type="journal article" year="1985">
Warncke, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE6EDCFE50FC92C2F7" box="[762,822,444,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6FA6FE50FB63C2F7" authority="Warncke, 1985" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1985" box="[896,1223,444,470]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6FA6FE50FC57C2F4" box="[896,1011,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. tapana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B7A4C62FFFE6821FE50FB64C2F7" author="Warncke" box="[1031,1216,444,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="7" refString="Warnicke, K. (1985) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna des Iran 19. - 20. Die gattungen Panurgus Pz. und Meliturgula Fr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Ven ezia, 34, 221 - 235." type="journal article" year="1985">
Warncke, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE68A2FE50FB64C2F7" box="[1156,1216,444,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
show a strong extension of the cuticle yellow coloration and nearly complete absence of the black marks. In contrast, the recently described species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6F75FDE0FB33C107" authority="Patiny, 2002" authorityName="Patiny" authorityYear="2002" box="[851,1175,524,550]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berangeriae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6F75FDE0FC5AC104" box="[851,1022,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. berangeriae</emphasis>
Patiny, 
<number id="3DA224AC4C62FFFE687AFDE0FB33C107" box="[1116,1175,524,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</taxonomicName>
and particularly 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6D6EFDD8FE55C16C" box="[328,497,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarziana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6D6EFDD8FE55C16C" box="[328,497,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F.schwarziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, show a strong reduction of the yellow markings. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6845FDD8FAA8C16C" box="[1123,1292,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarziana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6845FDD8FAA8C16C" box="[1123,1292,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F.schwarziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly entirely black. The 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6E69FDB0FD5CC154" box="[591,760,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarziana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6E69FDB0FD5CC154" box="[591,760,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F.schwarziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
body length (the smallest in the genus) is also interesting. Only one other species displays such a reduced size, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6FD8FD68FB0EC1BC" box="[1022,1194,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berangeriae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6FD8FD68FB0EC1BC" box="[1022,1194,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. berangeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD5368B4C62FFFE6D1EFD40FE29C0AF" blockId="5.[264,1323,284,910]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
From the biogeographic point of view, two characteristics of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6878FD40FA8EC1E4" box="[1118,1322,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6878FD40FA8EC1E4" box="[1118,1322,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Flavomeliturgula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
range must be underlined. Interestingly, the whole genus is distributed in South 
<collectingCountry id="F37D761B4C62FFFE68D2FD38FA82C1CF" box="[1268,1318,724,750]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Iran</collectingCountry>
, along the Zagros Mounts chain and Eastward in Baluchistan. The known data for 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6933FD10FE38C01C" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarziana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6933FD10FE38C01C" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. schwarziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also located in this area. Finally, now only three 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6802FCC8FB54C01C" box="[1060,1264,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6802FCC8FB54C01C" box="[1060,1264,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Flavomeliturgula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are known to be present in 
<collectingCountry id="F37D761B4C62FFFE6E58FCA0FD40C047" box="[638,740,844,870]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6ED7FCA0FC39C044" box="[753,925,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berangeriae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6ED7FCA0FC39C044" box="[753,925,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. berangeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE6FF1FCA0FBCDC044" box="[983,1129,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centaurea">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE6FF1FCA0FBCDC044" box="[983,1129,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. centaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D084C62FFFE685FFCA0FA8EC044" box="[1145,1322,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavomeliturgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarziana">
<emphasis id="B91EEA994C62FFFE685FFCA0FA8EC044" box="[1145,1322,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F. schwarziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the third.
</paragraph>
